      &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1268x713+129+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F90%2Fb0%2Fe2864a6b4dbe89b9cefe25466b65%2Fgames-we-love-screenshot.png 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1268x713+129+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F90%2Fb0%2Fe2864a6b4dbe89b9cefe25466b65%2Fgames-we-love-screenshot.png 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1268x713+129+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F90%2Fb0%2Fe2864a6b4dbe89b9cefe25466b65%2Fgames-we-love-screenshot.png 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1268x713+129+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F90%2Fb0%2Fe2864a6b4dbe89b9cefe25466b65%2Fgames-we-love-screenshot.png 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1268x713+129+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F90%2Fb0%2Fe2864a6b4dbe89b9cefe25466b65%2Fgames-we-love-screenshot.png 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1268x713+129+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F90%2Fb0%2Fe2864a6b4dbe89b9cefe25466b65%2Fgames-we-love-screenshot.png 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1268x713+129+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F90%2Fb0%2Fe2864a6b4dbe89b9cefe25466b65%2Fgames-we-love-screenshot.png 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1268x713+129+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F90%2Fb0%2Fe2864a6b4dbe89b9cefe25466b65%2Fgames-we-love-screenshot.png" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/png" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1268x713+129+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F90%2Fb0%2Fe2864a6b4dbe89b9cefe25466b65%2Fgames-we-love-screenshot.png" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1268x713+129+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F90%2Fb0%2Fe2864a6b4dbe89b9cefe25466b65%2Fgames-we-love-screenshot.png" class="img" alt="Screenshots or images of various games" loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Check out what &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/culture/"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NPR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt; is watching, reading and listening to this weekend:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🍿 Movies: &lt;/strong&gt;Afghan filmmaker Sahra Mani's new documentary &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/goats-and-soda/2024/12/03/g-s1-36446/afghanistan-women-taliban-bread-roses-apple-tv"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Bread &amp; Roses&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; tells the story of three women who are protesting the Taliban's erasure of women from political and public life.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;📺 TV:&lt;/strong&gt; In Netflix's &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/12/04/1216966354/in-the-madness-colman-domingo-gets-caught-up-in-a-convoluted-conspiracy"&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Madness&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, Colman Domingo plays Muncie Daniels, who finds himself on the run after he discovers a brutal murder and is framed for the crime.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;📚 Books:&lt;/strong&gt; NPR staff and book critics weighed in on their favorite titles for the annual &lt;a href="https://apps.npr.org/best-books/#view=covers&amp;year=2024"&gt;Books We Love&lt;/a&gt; guide. Here are a &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/12/02/nx-s1-5163778/best-novels-2024"&gt;dozen novels they are excited to share&lt;/a&gt; from this year.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🎵 Music:&lt;/strong&gt; NPR Music has rounded up a list featuring &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/12/04/g-s1-34686/best-songs-2024"&gt;124 of the best songs of the year&lt;/a&gt;. The collection has something for everyone and even allows you to discover songs through a single genre. Here's a &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/12/05/g-s1-36949/playlist-124-best-songs-of-2024"&gt;playlist&lt;/a&gt; for your streaming pleasure.&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🎮 Games:&lt;/strong&gt; From cozy puzzles to multiplayer sensations and grand adventures, NPR staff and contributors share their &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/07/16/g-s1-9554/best-games-2024-picked-by-npr-staff"&gt;favorite video games of 2024&lt;/a&gt; so far.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;❓ Quiz:&lt;/strong&gt; There has been a lot of news this week, from presidential pardons to a new word of the year. Maybe that is why I got a barely passing score on this quiz. Do &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/12/05/g-s1-36758/biden-pardon-bitcoin-brainrot-south-korea-pantone"&gt;you think you can do better&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-36951" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 8256;         --source-height: 4644;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8256x4644+0+430/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/