      <title>South Korea's president faces calls to be impeached. And, tips to avoid porch pirates</title>
      <author>Brittney Melton</author>
      <link>https://www.npr.org/2024/12/04/g-s1-36746/up-first-newsletter-south-korea-president-martial-law-porch-pirates</link>
      <comments>https://text.npr.org/2024/12/04/g-s1-36746/up-first-newsletter-south-korea-president-martial-law-porch-pirates</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.npr.org/2024/12/04/g-s1-36746/up-first-newsletter-south-korea-president-martial-law-porch-pirates</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 04 Dec 2024 12:58:57 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div id="storytext" class="storytext storylocation linkLocation"&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Good morning. You're reading the Up First newsletter. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/newsletter/news"&gt;Subscribe&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; here to get it delivered to your inbox, and &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/podcasts/510318/up-first/"&gt;listen&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; to the Up First podcast for all the news you need to start your day.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Today's top stories&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Opposition politicians in South Korea have submitted a &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/12/04/g-s1-36730/south-korea-president-martial-law"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;motion to impeach President Yoon Suk Yeol&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt; after his failed attempt &lt;/strong&gt;to place the country under martial law. This is the &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/12/03/g-s1-36594/south-korea-martial-law"&gt;first time a South Korean president has made such an attempt&lt;/a&gt; since the country went from military rule to democracy in 1987. It caught South Korean citizens and the U.S., a main ally, by surprise. Yoon said the opposition politicians who control parliament are paralyzing the government and subverting democracy, accusing them of aligning with North Korea.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-36613" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 7230;         --source-height: 4067;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7230x4067+0+377/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc6%2Fab%2Ffae0d43145049a55c50cdd695bd1%2Fgettyimages-2187499974.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7230x4067+0+377/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc6%2Fab%2Ffae0d43145049a55c50cdd695bd1%2Fgettyimages-2187499974.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7230x4067+0+377/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc6%2Fab%2Ffae0d43145049a55c50cdd695bd1%2Fgettyimages-2187499974.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7230x4067+0+377/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc6%2Fab%2Ffae0d43145049a55c50cdd695bd1%2Fgettyimages-2187499974.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7230x4067+0+377/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc6%2Fab%2Ffae0d43145049a55c50cdd695bd1%2Fgettyimages-2187499974.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7230x4067+0+377/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc6%2Fab%2Ffae0d43145049a55c50cdd695bd1%2Fgettyimages-2187499974.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7230x4067+0+377/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc6%2Fab%2Ffae0d43145049a55c50cdd695bd1%2Fgettyimages-2187499974.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7230x4067+0+377/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc6%2Fab%2Ffae0d43145049a55c50cdd695bd1%2Fgettyimages-2187499974.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7230x4067+0+377/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc6%2Fab%2Ffae0d43145049a55c50cdd695bd1%2Fgettyimages-2187499974.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7230x4067+0+377/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc6%2Fab%2Ffae0d43145049a55c50cdd695bd1%2Fgettyimages-2187499974.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7230x4067+0+377/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc6%2Fab%2Ffae0d43145049a55c50cdd695bd1%2Fgettyimages-2187499974.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7230x4067+0+377/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc6%2Fab%2Ffae0d43145049a55c50cdd695bd1%2Fgettyimages-2187499974.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7230x4067+0+377/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc6%2Fab%2Ffae0d43145049a55c50cdd695bd1%2Fgettyimages-2187499974.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7230x4067+0+377/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc6%2Fab%2Ffae0d43145049a55c50cdd695bd1%2Fgettyimages-2187499974.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7230x4067+0+377/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc6%2Fab%2Ffae0d43145049a55c50cdd695bd1%2Fgettyimages-2187499974.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7230x4067+0+377/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc6%2Fab%2Ffae0d43145049a55c50cdd695bd1%2Fgettyimages-2187499974.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7230x4067+0+377/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc6%2Fab%2Ffae0d43145049a55c50cdd695bd1%2Fgettyimages-2187499974.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7230x4067+0+377/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc6%2Fab%2Ffae0d43145049a55c50cdd695bd1%2Fgettyimages-2187499974.jpg" class="img" alt="A man holds the South Korea flag outside the National Assembly in Seoul on December 4, 2024, after President Yoon Suk Yeol declared emergency martial law." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 A man holds the South Korea flag outside the National Assembly in Seoul on December 4, 2024, after President Yoon Suk Yeol declared emergency martial law.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Anthony Wallace/AFP via Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧 &lt;strong&gt;"People here have just expressed such disbelief that such a thing could happen in South Korea in 2024," &lt;/strong&gt;NPR's Anthony Kuhn, who is in Seoul, tells &lt;em&gt;Up First&lt;/em&gt;. Even though martial law was declared several times before 1987, South Koreans today are more skeptical of attempts to deprive their rights in the name of a communist threat. Benjamin Engel, a political scientist and visiting professor at Dankook University outside of Seoul, described what President Yoon was &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1216966360:1263129312"&gt;attempting as a coup or self-coup&lt;/a&gt;. This means Yoon, who has struggled to get his policies and budget through parliament despite being democratically elected, enacted martial law to hang on to and increase his power through an attempt to roll back civil liberties.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A battle for transgender children's rights will be front and center at the Supreme Court today. &lt;/strong&gt;At issue is a Tennessee law that &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/12/04/nx-s1-5179003/supreme-court-gender-affirming-care-trans-kids"&gt;blocks minors from accessing gender-affirming care&lt;/a&gt;. Within the last three years, over two dozen states have enacted laws that ban puberty blockers, hormones and other treatments for minors who say their gender doesn't align with their sex at birth. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧 &lt;strong&gt;Three Tennessee families are challenging the law. They say it unconstitutionally discriminates based on sex because &lt;/strong&gt;the banned medications are legal when used to treat other conditions in minors, according to NPR's Nina Totenberg. Those conditions range from chronic diseases like endometriosis to early or late-onset puberty. Totenberg says major medical organizations that deal with gender-affirming care are on the side of providing treatments for children, but with guardrails. Critics of the treatments say the science is &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1216966360:1263129312"&gt;very unsettled in its long-term implications&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The French government could fall today as it faces a no-confidence vote brought by the far left and far right. &lt;/strong&gt;If they get the votes needed to pass in the lower house of parliament, Prime Minister Michel Barnier, who has been in power less than three months, could be ousted. At issue is the 2025 budget, which attempts to address France's spiraling deficit. Barnier pushed it through parliament this week without holding a vote by using an emergency clause. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧 &lt;strong&gt;The far-left party has said it would punish Barnier if he used the emergency clause to pass the bill&lt;/strong&gt;, NPR's Eleanor Beardsley says. Barnier thought he could succeed because Marine Le Pen, leader of the far-right National Rally party, said she would stand by the government. National Rally is the biggest party in parliament. Le Pen changed her mind over the weekend. Now, &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1216966360:1263129312"&gt;both sides are joining forces to bring down&lt;/a&gt; the more centrist prime minister. If the government falls, President Emmanuel Macron will have to name someone else for the role.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Life advice&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-36455" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 4038;         --source-height: 2271;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4038x2271+0+206/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2Fdd%2F68ba941f4871bba294449b2d2f3c%2Fap091214118688.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4038x2271+0+206/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2Fdd%2F68ba941f4871bba294449b2d2f3c%2Fap091214118688.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4038x2271+0+206/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2Fdd%2F68ba941f4871bba294449b2d2f3c%2Fap091214118688.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4038x2271+0+206/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2Fdd%2F68ba941f4871bba294449b2d2f3c%2Fap091214118688.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4038x2271+0+206/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2Fdd%2F68ba941f4871bba294449b2d2f3c%2Fap091214118688.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4038x2271+0+206/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2Fdd%2F68ba941f4871bba294449b2d2f3c%2Fap091214118688.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4038x2271+0+206/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2Fdd%2F68ba941f4871bba294449b2d2f3c%2Fap091214118688.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4038x2271+0+206/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2Fdd%2F68ba941f4871bba294449b2d2f3c%2Fap091214118688.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4038x2271+0+206/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2Fdd%2F68ba941f4871bba294449b2d2f3c%2Fap091214118688.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4038x2271+0+206/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2Fdd%2F68ba941f4871bba294449b2d2f3c%2Fap091214118688.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4038x2271+0+206/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2Fdd%2F68ba941f4871bba294449b2d2f3c%2Fap091214118688.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4038x2271+0+206/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2Fdd%2F68ba941f4871bba294449b2d2f3c%2Fap091214118688.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4038x2271+0+206/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2Fdd%2F68ba941f4871bba294449b2d2f3c%2Fap091214118688.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4038x2271+0+206/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2Fdd%2F68ba941f4871bba294449b2d2f3c%2Fap091214118688.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4038x2271+0+206/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2Fdd%2F68ba941f4871bba294449b2d2f3c%2Fap091214118688.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4038x2271+0+206/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2Fdd%2F68ba941f4871bba294449b2d2f3c%2Fap091214118688.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4038x2271+0+206/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2Fdd%2F68ba941f4871bba294449b2d2f3c%2Fap091214118688.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4038x2271+0+206/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F49%2Fdd%2F68ba941f4871bba294449b2d2f3c%2Fap091214118688.jpg" class="img" alt="In this 2009 file photo, a FedEx driver delivers a package in the Queens section of New York." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 In this 2009 file photo, a FedEx driver delivers a package in the Queens section of New York.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Mark Lennihan/AP                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Local officials and retailers are warning Americans to remain vigilant this holiday season and not fall victim to porch pirates&lt;/strong&gt;, who steal packages from homes. More than 120 million packages were stolen last year across the U.S., according to a SafeWise analysis. Here are some &lt;a href="http://www.npr.org/2024/12/03/nx-s1-5213653/protect-packages-porch-pirates"&gt;steps you can take to protect your packages&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;📦 &lt;strong&gt;Thieves commonly like to steal &lt;/strong&gt;electronics, shoes and other expensive items.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;📦 &lt;strong&gt;See if you can &lt;/strong&gt;have the items from popular brands shipped in packaging that hides the label.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;📦&lt;strong&gt; Amazon recommends customers provide&lt;/strong&gt; a specific location to deliver the package. Ideally, it's one hidden from view.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Read the &lt;/strong&gt;complete &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/12/03/nx-s1-5213653/protect-packages-porch-pirates"&gt;list of advice to help&lt;/a&gt; protect your items, and learn what you can do if they are stolen.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Picture show&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-36417" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 9500;         --source-height: 5344;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/9500x5344+2+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F02%2F947fd81c439688e933e7dde5161e%2Fwhitehouseholidaydecor-sofiaseidel-3.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/9500x5344+2+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F02%2F947fd81c439688e933e7dde5161e%2Fwhitehouseholidaydecor-sofiaseidel-3.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/9500x5344+2+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F02%2F947fd81c439688e933e7dde5161e%2Fwhitehouseholidaydecor-sofiaseidel-3.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/9500x5344+2+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F02%2F947fd81c439688e933e7dde5161e%2Fwhitehouseholidaydecor-sofiaseidel-3.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/9500x5344+2+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F02%2F947fd81c439688e933e7dde5161e%2Fwhitehouseholidaydecor-sofiaseidel-3.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/9500x5344+2+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F02%2F947fd81c439688e933e7dde5161e%2Fwhitehouseholidaydecor-sofiaseidel-3.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/9500x5344+2+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F02%2F947fd81c439688e933e7dde5161e%2Fwhitehouseholidaydecor-sofiaseidel-3.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/9500x5344+2+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F02%2F947fd81c439688e933e7dde5161e%2Fwhitehouseholidaydecor-sofiaseidel-3.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/9500x5344+2+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F02%2F947fd81c439688e933e7dde5161e%2Fwhitehouseholidaydecor-sofiaseidel-3.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/9500x5344+2+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F02%2F947fd81c439688e933e7dde5161e%2Fwhitehouseholidaydecor-sofiaseidel-3.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/9500x5344+2+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F02%2F947fd81c439688e933e7dde5161e%2Fwhitehouseholidaydecor-sofiaseidel-3.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/9500x5344+2+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F02%2F947fd81c439688e933e7dde5161e%2Fwhitehouseholidaydecor-sofiaseidel-3.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/9500x5344+2+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F02%2F947fd81c439688e933e7dde5161e%2Fwhitehouseholidaydecor-sofiaseidel-3.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/9500x5344+2+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F02%2F947fd81c439688e933e7dde5161e%2Fwhitehouseholidaydecor-sofiaseidel-3.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/9500x5344+2+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F02%2F947fd81c439688e933e7dde5161e%2Fwhitehouseholidaydecor-sofiaseidel-3.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/9500x5344+2+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F02%2F947fd81c439688e933e7dde5161e%2Fwhitehouseholidaydecor-sofiaseidel-3.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/9500x5344+2+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F02%2F947fd81c439688e933e7dde5161e%2Fwhitehouseholidaydecor-sofiaseidel-3.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/9500x5344+2+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F30%2F02%2F947fd81c439688e933e7dde5161e%2Fwhitehouseholidaydecor-sofiaseidel-3.jpg" class="img" alt="Musicians perform in the East Colonnade of the White House in Washington, as everything is decorated for the holidays, Monday, Dec. 2, 2024" loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Musicians perform in the East Colonnade of the White House in Washington, D.C, Monday, Dec. 2, 2024                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Sofia Seidel/NPR                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;First lady Jill Biden has decked the halls of the White House for the &lt;/strong&gt;family's last Christmas of President Biden's presidency. The theme of this year's decor is "A Season of Peace and Light." More than 300 volunteers spent the past week decorating the White House's public spaces and its 83 Christmas trees with nearly 10,000 feet of ribbon, over 28,000 ornaments, more than 2,200 paper doves and around 165,000 lights, according to the Associated Press. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;📷 &lt;strong&gt;See photos&lt;/strong&gt; of the &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/the-picture-show/2024/12/02/g-s1-36441/photos-biden-white-house-christmas-decorations"&gt;White House Christmas decorations on display&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="res1140261645" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 2127;         --source-height: 1196;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/12/02/ap22336311329418_wide-6e7f149eb387eb67a1b2eb3feccbbb4a9d5871e1.jpg?s=400&amp;c=85&amp;f=webp 400w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/12/02/ap22336311329418_wide-6e7f149eb387eb67a1b2eb3feccbbb4a9d5871e1.jpg?s=600&amp;c=85&amp;f=webp 600w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/12/02/ap22336311329418_wide-6e7f149eb387eb67a1b2eb3feccbbb4a9d5871e1.jpg?s=800&amp;c=85&amp;f=webp 800w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/12/02/ap22336311329418_wide-6e7f149eb387eb67a1b2eb3feccbbb4a9d5871e1.jpg?s=900&amp;c=85&amp;f=webp 900w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/12/02/ap22336311329418_wide-6e7f149eb387eb67a1b2eb3feccbbb4a9d5871e1.jpg?s=1200&amp;c=85&amp;f=webp 1200w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/12/02/ap22336311329418_wide-6e7f149eb387eb67a1b2eb3feccbbb4a9d5871e1.jpg?s=1600&amp;c=85&amp;f=webp 1600w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/12/02/ap22336311329418_wide-6e7f149eb387eb67a1b2eb3feccbbb4a9d5871e1.jpg?s=1800&amp;c=85&amp;f=webp 1800w" data-template="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/12/02/ap22336311329418_wide-6e7f149eb387eb67a1b2eb3feccbbb4a9d5871e1.jpg?s={width}&amp;c={quality}&amp;f={format}" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/12/02/ap22336311329418_wide-6e7f149eb387eb67a1b2eb3feccbbb4a9d5871e1.jpg?s=400&amp;c=85&amp;f=jpeg 400w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/12/02/ap22336311329418_wide-6e7f149eb387eb67a1b2eb3feccbbb4a9d5871e1.jpg?s=600&amp;c=85&amp;f=jpeg 600w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/12/02/ap22336311329418_wide-6e7f149eb387eb67a1b2eb3feccbbb4a9d5871e1.jpg?s=800&amp;c=85&amp;f=jpeg 800w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/12/02/ap22336311329418_wide-6e7f149eb387eb67a1b2eb3feccbbb4a9d5871e1.jpg?s=900&amp;c=85&amp;f=jpeg 900w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/12/02/ap22336311329418_wide-6e7f149eb387eb67a1b2eb3feccbbb4a9d5871e1.jpg?s=1200&amp;c=85&amp;f=jpeg 1200w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/12/02/ap22336311329418_wide-6e7f149eb387eb67a1b2eb3feccbbb4a9d5871e1.jpg?s=1600&amp;c=85&amp;f=jpeg 1600w, https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/12/02/ap22336311329418_wide-6e7f149eb387eb67a1b2eb3feccbbb4a9d5871e1.jpg?s=1800&amp;c=85&amp;f=jpeg 1800w" data-template="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/12/02/ap22336311329418_wide-6e7f149eb387eb67a1b2eb3feccbbb4a9d5871e1.jpg?s={width}&amp;c={quality}&amp;f={format}" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/12/02/ap22336311329418_wide-6e7f149eb387eb67a1b2eb3feccbbb4a9d5871e1.jpg?s=1100&amp;c=50&amp;f=jpeg" data-template="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2022/12/02/ap22336311329418_wide-6e7f149eb387eb67a1b2eb3feccbbb4a9d5871e1.jpg?s={width}&amp;c={quality}&amp;f={format}" class="img" alt="Elton John performs on the South Lawn of the White House in Washington, Friday, Sept. 23, 2022." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt;          &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Elton John performs on the South Lawn of the White House in Washington, Friday, Sept. 23, 2022.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Susan Walsh/AP                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;      &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;On the opening night of the musical &lt;em&gt;The Devil Wears Prada&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, Elton John said the effects of an &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/12/03/nx-s1-5214382/elton-john-eyesight-devil-wears-prada"&gt;eye infection sharply limited his eyesight&lt;/a&gt; to the point that he couldn't see the performance he wrote the score for.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nearly 500 journalists at the&lt;em&gt; Guardian&lt;/em&gt; and its sister paper&lt;/strong&gt;, the&lt;em&gt; Observer&lt;/em&gt;, are on strike to &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/12/04/nx-s1-5213914/guardian-strike-observer-sale"&gt;protest the &lt;em&gt;Observer&lt;/em&gt;'s planned sale&lt;/a&gt; to a digital startup.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A court ruled that Idaho can partially enforce its "abortion trafficking law,"&lt;/strong&gt; preventing adults from "harboring" or "transporting" minors out of the state to &lt;a href="https://www.boisestatepublicradio.org/health/2024-12-03/abortion-trafficking-injunction-idaho-freedom-of-speech"&gt;terminate a pregnancy without&lt;/a&gt; their parents' consent. (via &lt;a href="https://www.boisestatepublicradio.org/"&gt;Boise State Public Radio&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
