      <pubDate>Fri, 29 Nov 2024 12:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div id="storytext" class="storytext storylocation linkLocation"&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Good morning. You're reading the Up First newsletter. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/newsletter/news"&gt;Subscribe&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; here to get it delivered to your inbox, and &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/podcasts/510318/up-first/"&gt;listen&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; to the Up First podcast for all the news you need to start your day.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Books we love: Staff Favorites&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Good morning! &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/348740829/andrew-limbong"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Andrew Limbong&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; here, books reporter at NPR. I'm subbing in this newsletter to tell you about &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://apps.npr.org/best-books/#view=covers&amp;year=2024"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Books We Love&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;, our year-end round-up of our favorite reads. The 2024 edition lists more than 350 books. Which just means there's something for everyone here. Poke around the platform to discover a book for you or someone you love (or are gift-shopping for). And, scroll down for a few of the top staff picks this year. If you want to shout out your favorite, the email is &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="http://bookoftheday@npr.org"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;bookoftheday@npr.org&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; and subscribe to &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://n.pr/4awM8Fv"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;NPR's Book of the Day podcast&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-35919" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 1934;         --source-height: 1088;     " &gt;     &lt;a href="https://apps.npr.org/best-books/"&gt;             &lt;picture&gt;                 &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1934x1088+0+802/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2Fc3%2F3f5428d94d1bb121eddceb35265a%2F2024-books-we-love-covers.png 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1934x1088+0+802/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2Fc3%2F3f5428d94d1bb121eddceb35265a%2F2024-books-we-love-covers.png 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1934x1088+0+802/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2Fc3%2F3f5428d94d1bb121eddceb35265a%2F2024-books-we-love-covers.png 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1934x1088+0+802/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2Fc3%2F3f5428d94d1bb121eddceb35265a%2F2024-books-we-love-covers.png 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1934x1088+0+802/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2Fc3%2F3f5428d94d1bb121eddceb35265a%2F2024-books-we-love-covers.png 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1934x1088+0+802/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2Fc3%2F3f5428d94d1bb121eddceb35265a%2F2024-books-we-love-covers.png 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1934x1088+0+802/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2Fc3%2F3f5428d94d1bb121eddceb35265a%2F2024-books-we-love-covers.png 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1934x1088+0+802/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2Fc3%2F3f5428d94d1bb121eddceb35265a%2F2024-books-we-love-covers.png" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;                 &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1934x1088+0+802/resize/400/quality/85/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2Fc3%2F3f5428d94d1bb121eddceb35265a%2F2024-books-we-love-covers.png 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1934x1088+0+802/resize/600/quality/85/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2Fc3%2F3f5428d94d1bb121eddceb35265a%2F2024-books-we-love-covers.png 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1934x1088+0+802/resize/800/quality/85/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2Fc3%2F3f5428d94d1bb121eddceb35265a%2F2024-books-we-love-covers.png 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1934x1088+0+802/resize/900/quality/85/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2Fc3%2F3f5428d94d1bb121eddceb35265a%2F2024-books-we-love-covers.png 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1934x1088+0+802/resize/1200/quality/85/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2Fc3%2F3f5428d94d1bb121eddceb35265a%2F2024-books-we-love-covers.png 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1934x1088+0+802/resize/1600/quality/85/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2Fc3%2F3f5428d94d1bb121eddceb35265a%2F2024-books-we-love-covers.png 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1934x1088+0+802/resize/1800/quality/85/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2Fc3%2F3f5428d94d1bb121eddceb35265a%2F2024-books-we-love-covers.png 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1934x1088+0+802/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2Fc3%2F3f5428d94d1bb121eddceb35265a%2F2024-books-we-love-covers.png" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/png" /&gt;                 &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1934x1088+0+802/resize/1100/quality/50/format/png/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2Fc3%2F3f5428d94d1bb121eddceb35265a%2F2024-books-we-love-covers.png" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1934x1088+0+802/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2Fc3%2F3f5428d94d1bb121eddceb35265a%2F2024-books-we-love-covers.png" class="img" alt="An assortment of book covers from the 2024 edition of Books We Love." loading="lazy" /&gt;             &lt;/picture&gt;     &lt;/a&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OK, technically, &lt;em&gt;hundreds&lt;/em&gt; of the selections in Books We Love are made by staff.&lt;/strong&gt; That's kind of the whole shtick! Here are a few 2024 books that got LOTS of votes from our NPR colleagues.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;📚 All Fours&lt;/em&gt; by Miranda July:&lt;/strong&gt; Is it just me, or are we hearing a lot more about perimenopause since this novel dropped? It's about an unnamed artist who leaves her husband and kid to go on a wild trip exploring the edges of her desires. Wailin Wong, host of NPR's The Indicator podcast, says the protagonist makes choices "that you may find &lt;a href="https://apps.npr.org/best-books/#year=2024&amp;book=18"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;hilarious, relatable, or infuriating&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, but they are never boring."&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;📚 &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Funny Story&lt;/em&gt; by Emily Henry: &lt;/strong&gt;You've probably spotted this book at your local bookstore. If you haven't perused it yet, it's a rom-com from one of the reigning champs of the genre. NPR Growth Editor Arielle Retting explains the plot as "&lt;a href="https://apps.npr.org/best-books/#year=2024&amp;book=82"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The ex of my enemy is my friend&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, I guess?"&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;📚 &lt;em&gt;Martyr!&lt;/em&gt; by Kaveh Akbar:&lt;/strong&gt; A debut novel that came out with a splash this year, getting nominated for a National Book Award. It's about a guy obsessed with death. The book is filled with sadness and anger. But also, every review of the book I've read points to how funny it is. NPR Wild Card Editor Dave Blanchard writes, "It could &lt;a href="https://apps.npr.org/best-books/#year=2024&amp;book=150"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;leave you in tears&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; of laughter or of sorrow. Or most likely both."&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;These are just a tiny fraction of the hundreds of books recommended by our staffers and critics.&lt;/strong&gt; Over in the NPR Books newsletter, we'll be showcasing different genres and categories through the end of the year. Biographies, thrillers, cookbooks and more! &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/newsletter/books"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Subscribe here&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; if you want to keep the recommendations coming.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Black Friday stories you may have missed&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-35906" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 5846;         --source-height: 3288;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcse