px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5846x3288+0+151/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe7%2Fb2%2Fa5a805ed42148cf34df60e83e705%2Fgettyimages-1185355962.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5846x3288+0+151/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe7%2Fb2%2Fa5a805ed42148cf34df60e83e705%2Fgettyimages-1185355962.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5846x3288+0+151/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe7%2Fb2%2Fa5a805ed42148cf34df60e83e705%2Fgettyimages-1185355962.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5846x3288+0+151/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe7%2Fb2%2Fa5a805ed42148cf34df60e83e705%2Fgettyimages-1185355962.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5846x3288+0+151/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe7%2Fb2%2Fa5a805ed42148cf34df60e83e705%2Fgettyimages-1185355962.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5846x3288+0+151/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe7%2Fb2%2Fa5a805ed42148cf34df60e83e705%2Fgettyimages-1185355962.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5846x3288+0+151/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe7%2Fb2%2Fa5a805ed42148cf34df60e83e705%2Fgettyimages-1185355962.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5846x3288+0+151/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe7%2Fb2%2Fa5a805ed42148cf34df60e83e705%2Fgettyimages-1185355962.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5846x3288+0+151/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe7%2Fb2%2Fa5a805ed42148cf34df60e83e705%2Fgettyimages-1185355962.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5846x3288+0+151/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe7%2Fb2%2Fa5a805ed42148cf34df60e83e705%2Fgettyimages-1185355962.jpg" class="img" alt="Deals are the name of the game this holiday season as more people are planning to shop between Black Friday and Cyber Monday, hoping for bargains." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Deals are the name of the game this holiday season as more people are planning to shop between Black Friday and Cyber Monday, hoping for bargains.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Sarah Silbiger/Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;People are expected to spend a record of up to $989 billion this holiday season. &lt;/strong&gt;Higher prices explain some of the higher spending, but it's not the whole story. A greater share of people also plan to splurge this holiday season, according to a survey by market research firm Circana. Here's &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/11/27/nx-s1-5206495/black-friday-deals-2024-shopping-economy"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;what to expect&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; from this year's Black Friday and holiday shopping season.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you're looking for some great deals today, try looking beyond the big stores like Amazon, Target or Best Buy.&lt;/strong&gt; Some of the best sales are hiding in plain sight, if you know where to look. Joanie Demer of the website thekrazycouponlady.com &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1215057932:1215057933"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;shares her bargain-hunting tips&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;em&gt;Morning Edition. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Music lovers have something to look forward to today.&lt;/strong&gt; Record stores across the country are offering special releases as part of what they call Record Store Day Black Friday. The billion-dollar vinyl record industry has been growing steadily over the years. Now the manufacturers who press these records &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=nx-s1-5203053:nx-s1-5273248-1"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;face competitors&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; from abroad.&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Not into shopping 'till you drop? &lt;/strong&gt;Ditch the shopping cart and try one of these &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2023/11/20/1213214810/black-friday-2023-alternatives-shopping"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;four ways to observe Black Friday&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; without spending money.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Weekend picks&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-35552" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 4000;         --source-height: 2250;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F35%2F94%2F15f55e0a42f19192e0ada4adfebe%2F20241118-hammar-me-mohammad-rasoulof-1.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F35%2F94%2F15f55e0a42f19192e0ada4adfebe%2F20241118-hammar-me-mohammad-rasoulof-1.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F35%2F94%2F15f55e0a42f19192e0ada4adfebe%2F20241118-hammar-me-mohammad-rasoulof-1.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F35%2F94%2F15f55e0a42f19192e0ada4adfebe%2F20241118-hammar-me-mohammad-rasoulof-1.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F35%2F94%2F15f55e0a42f19192e0ada4adfebe%2F20241118-hammar-me-mohammad-rasoulof-1.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F35%2F94%2F15f55e0a42f19192e0ada4adfebe%2F20241118-hammar-me-mohammad-rasoulof-1.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F35%2F94%2F15f55e0a42f19192e0ada4adfebe%2F20241118-hammar-me-mohammad-rasoulof-1.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F35%2F94%2F15f55e0a42f19192e0ada4adfebe%2F20241118-hammar-me-mohammad-rasoulof-1.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F35%2F94%2F15f55e0a42f19192e0ada4adfebe%2F20241118-hammar-me-mohammad-rasoulof-1.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F35%2F94%2F15f55e0a42f19192e0ada4adfebe%2F20241118-hammar-me-mohammad-rasoulof-1.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F35%2F94%2F15f55e0a42f19192e0ada4adfebe%2F20241118-hammar-me-mohammad-rasoulof-1.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F35%2F94%2F15f55e0a42f19192e0ada4adfebe%2F20241118-hammar-me-mohammad-rasoulof-1.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F35%2F94%2F15f55e0a42f19192e0ada4adfebe%2F20241118-hammar-me-mohammad-rasoulof-1.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F35%2F94%2F15f55e0a42f19192e0ada4adfebe%2F20241118-hammar-me-mohammad-rasoulof-1.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F35%2F94%2F15f55e0a42f19192e0ada4adfebe%2F20241118-hammar-me-mohammad-rasoulof-1.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F35%2F94%2F15f55e0a42f19192e0ada4adfebe%2F20241118-hammar-me-mohammad-rasoulof-1.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F35%2F94%2F15f55e0a42f19192e0ada4adfebe%2F20241118-hammar-me-mohammad-rasoulof-1.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F35%2F94%2F15f55e0a42f19192e0ada4adfebe%2F20241118-hammar-me-mohammad-rasoulof-1.jpg" class="img" alt="Iranian dissident filmmaker Mohammad Rasoulof speaks with NPR in New York in November 2024." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Iranian dissident filmmaker Mohammad Rasoulof speaks with NPR in New York in November 2024.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Nickolai Hammar/NPR                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Check out what &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/culture/"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NPR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt; is watching, reading and listening to this weekend:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🍿 Movies: &lt;/strong&gt;Filmmaker Mohammad Rasoulof's &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/11/26/nx-s1-5163638/mohammad-rasoulof-iran-seed-of-sacred-fig"&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Seed of the Sacred Fig&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; focuses on a family of four in Tehran that grows increasingly divided over the daughters' support for the Woman, Life, Freedom movement. Rasoulof talked with Morning Edition about the making of the new political thriller and how he escaped Iran on foot.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;📺 TV: &lt;/strong&gt;Ted Danson stars in &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=nx-s1-5163638:nx-s1-5262286-1"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;A Man on the Inside&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; as a lonely widower hired by a private investigator to live undercover in a senior living facility to find who stole a precious item.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;📚 Books: &lt;/strong&gt;Former German Chancellor Angela Merkel's new memoir &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1215540862:1262727141"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Freedom&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; shines a light on her life and political journey. She is the only woman to lead Germany and is one of the longest-serving leaders in the European Union. She talks with NPR's Mary Louise Kelly to discuss her book, feminism, Vladimir Putin and more.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🎵 Music:&lt;/strong&gt; Kendrick Lamar's surprise album &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/11/25/g-s1-35740/kendrick-lamars-rules-for-raps-new-administration"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;GNX&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; lays out his agenda: truth-telling and fraud-exposing, going scorched-earth and drawing out the fence-sitters in a culture war he is hell-bent on ending.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🍫 Food:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/11/21/nx-s1-5182873/a-viral-chocolate-bar-from-dubai-is-here-to-stay"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dubai chocolate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;is the new craze and it's not just a phase, with franchises like Baskin-Robbins adding it to their menu. The chocolate bars are like KitKats, but filled with pistachios and aromatic pistachio nougat.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Carol Ritchie. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
