      <title>How Trump wants to cut spending. And, possible Israel-Hezbollah ceasefire deal</title>
      <author>Brittney Melton</author>
      <link>https://www.npr.org/2024/11/26/g-s1-35883/up-first-newsletter-donald-trump-russ-vought-impoundment-tool-israel-hezbollah-ceasefire</link>
      <comments>https://text.npr.org/2024/11/26/g-s1-35883/up-first-newsletter-donald-trump-russ-vought-impoundment-tool-israel-hezbollah-ceasefire</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.npr.org/2024/11/26/g-s1-35883/up-first-newsletter-donald-trump-russ-vought-impoundment-tool-israel-hezbollah-ceasefire</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 26 Nov 2024 13:00:45 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div id="storytext" class="storytext storylocation linkLocation"&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Good morning. You're reading the Up First newsletter. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/newsletter/news"&gt;Subscribe&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; here to get it delivered to your inbox, and &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/podcasts/510318/up-first/"&gt;listen&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; to the Up First podcast for all the news you need to start your day.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Today's top stories&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A ceasefire between Israel and the militant group Hezbollah in Lebanon may be imminent.&lt;/strong&gt; Officials from both countries are set to&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;hold meetings and vote on a proposal this week. For more than a year, Israel and Hezbollah had been fighting a low-level conflict. In September, Israel widened its airstrikes on Lebanon and sent in ground troops, killing most Hezbollah leaders and devastating the country.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-29195" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 4464;         --source-height: 2511;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4464x2511+0+233/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2e%2F37%2F3b968d484c4a8dd648970aa703e6%2Fgettyimages-2179018030.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4464x2511+0+233/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2e%2F37%2F3b968d484c4a8dd648970aa703e6%2Fgettyimages-2179018030.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4464x2511+0+233/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2e%2F37%2F3b968d484c4a8dd648970aa703e6%2Fgettyimages-2179018030.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4464x2511+0+233/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2e%2F37%2F3b968d484c4a8dd648970aa703e6%2Fgettyimages-2179018030.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4464x2511+0+233/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2e%2F37%2F3b968d484c4a8dd648970aa703e6%2Fgettyimages-2179018030.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4464x2511+0+233/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2e%2F37%2F3b968d484c4a8dd648970aa703e6%2Fgettyimages-2179018030.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4464x2511+0+233/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2e%2F37%2F3b968d484c4a8dd648970aa703e6%2Fgettyimages-2179018030.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4464x2511+0+233/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2e%2F37%2F3b968d484c4a8dd648970aa703e6%2Fgettyimages-2179018030.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4464x2511+0+233/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2e%2F37%2F3b968d484c4a8dd648970aa703e6%2Fgettyimages-2179018030.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4464x2511+0+233/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2e%2F37%2F3b968d484c4a8dd648970aa703e6%2Fgettyimages-2179018030.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4464x2511+0+233/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2e%2F37%2F3b968d484c4a8dd648970aa703e6%2Fgettyimages-2179018030.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4464x2511+0+233/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2e%2F37%2F3b968d484c4a8dd648970aa703e6%2Fgettyimages-2179018030.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4464x2511+0+233/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2e%2F37%2F3b968d484c4a8dd648970aa703e6%2Fgettyimages-2179018030.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4464x2511+0+233/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2e%2F37%2F3b968d484c4a8dd648970aa703e6%2Fgettyimages-2179018030.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4464x2511+0+233/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2e%2F37%2F3b968d484c4a8dd648970aa703e6%2Fgettyimages-2179018030.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4464x2511+0+233/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2e%2F37%2F3b968d484c4a8dd648970aa703e6%2Fgettyimages-2179018030.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4464x2511+0+233/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2e%2F37%2F3b968d484c4a8dd648970aa703e6%2Fgettyimages-2179018030.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4464x2511+0+233/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2e%2F37%2F3b968d484c4a8dd648970aa703e6%2Fgettyimages-2179018030.jpg" class="img" alt="People inspect the damage at the site of an overnight Israeli airstrike that targeted a branch of the Al-Qard Al-Hassan finance group in Beirut&amp;#039;s southern suburbs on Monday." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 People inspect the damage at the site of an overnight Israeli airstrike that targeted a branch of the Al-Qard Al-Hassan finance group in Beirut's southern suburbs on Monday.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          -/AFP via Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧 &lt;strong&gt;It's not a done deal, but it would be an initial two-month ceasefire involving Israeli troops withdrawing from Lebanon and&lt;/strong&gt; Hezbollah pulling its fighters and weapons north of the Litani River, NPR's Lauren Frayer tells &lt;em&gt;Up First&lt;/em&gt;. The terms are almost exactly the same as the ceasefire in 2006 — the last time Israel invaded Lebanon. &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1215240074:1262856053"&gt;One stumbling block to negotiations is&lt;/a&gt; that Israel wants the freedom to attack Hezbollah if it believes it's violating the deal. If the U.S. grants Israel the right to strike pre-emptively, Lebanon could see it as a violation of its sovereignty.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;President-elect Donald Trump wants to use a little-known tool called presidential impoundment to deliver on his promise&lt;/strong&gt; of big cuts in government spending. Impoundment is when the president holds back money that Congress has approved for a specific purpose. On Friday, he announced his pick for the person to &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/11/22/nx-s1-5193351/trump-russ-vought-omb-budget-director"&gt;wield that power&lt;/a&gt;: Russ Vought, a key architect of Project 2025. He has been tapped to lead the White House Office of Management and Budget. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧 &lt;strong&gt;Trump and his allies argue that a president has — or should have — the right not to spend those funds. &lt;/strong&gt;This has raised alarms across D.C. that Trump may try to overstep his power, NPR's Franco Ordoñez says. A 1974 law called the Impoundment Control Act &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1215240074:1262856053"&gt;could stand in the way of his plans&lt;/a&gt; as it requires a president to spend money as Congress directs. During his first term in office, Congress objected when Trump impounded foreign aid for Ukraine. Things could be different this time around with a Republican-controlled Congress.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;➡️ &lt;strong&gt;Trump has promised to put more money back in Americans' pockets &lt;/strong&gt;by lowering taxes. Here are &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/11/25/nx-s1-5203099/trump-tax-cuts-social-security-tipped-income"&gt;three ways it could impact you&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Black women have been essential when it comes to turning out voters. But after Vice President Harris lost the chance to&lt;/strong&gt; become the first Black woman president, many Black women organizers say they're exhausted. Some have decided to step back, and it's unclear when they're ready to return. Christina Greer, a political science professor at Fordham University, says if enough organizers take a step back or rethink some of their past strategies, it could affect U.S. politics. Here's what some &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/11/25/nx-s1-5191697/black-women-political-organizers-trump-election"&gt;Black female organizers have to say about&lt;/a&gt; their work mobilizing voters, the results of this election and what might be next for them.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Today's listen&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-35884" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 624;         --source-height: 351;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/599x337+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcf%2F74%2F0b3679a4474a8a8f96fae6a8ee72%2Fkimdeal-wide-d6096c82910f34fc30b8d9cb7a8af56b8e2c2fe8.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/599x337+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcf%2F74%2F0b3679a4474a8a8f96fae6a8ee72%2Fkimdeal-wide-d6096c82910f34fc30b8d9cb7a8af56b8e2c2fe8.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/599x337+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcf%2F74%2F0b3679a4474a8a8f96fae6a8ee72%2Fkimdeal-wide-d6096c82910f34fc30b8d9cb7a8af56b8e2c2fe8.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/599x337+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcf%2F74%2F0b3679a4474a8a8f96fae6a8ee72%2Fkimdeal-wide-d6096c82910f34fc30b8d9cb7a8af56b8e2c2fe8.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/599x337+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcf%2F74%2F0b3679a4474a8a8f96fae6a8ee72%2Fkimdeal-wide-d6096c82910f34fc30b8d9cb7a8af56b8e2c2fe8.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/599x337+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcf%2F74%2F0b3679a4474a8a8f96fae6a8ee72%2Fkimdeal-wide-d6096c82910f34fc30b8d9cb7a8af56b8e2c2fe8.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/599x337+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcf%2F74%2F0b3679a4474a8a8f96fae6a8ee72%2Fkimdeal-wide-d6096c82910f34fc30b8d9cb7a8af56b8e2c2fe8.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/599x337+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcf%2F74%2F0b3679a4474a8a8f96fae6a8ee72%2Fkimdeal-wide-d6096c82910f34fc30b8d9cb7a8af56b8e2c2fe8.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/599x337+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcf%2F74%2F0b3679a4474a8a8f96fae6a8ee72%2Fkimdeal-wide-d6096c82910f34fc30b8d9cb7a8af56b8e2c2fe8.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/599x337+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcf%2F74%2F0b3679a4474a8a8f96fae6a8ee72%2Fkimdeal-wide-d6096c82910f34fc30b8d9cb7a8af56b8e2c2fe8.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/599x337+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcf%2F74%2F0b3679a4474a8a8f96fae6a8ee72%2Fkimdeal-wide-d6096c82910f34fc30b8d9cb7a8af56b8e2c2fe8.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/599x337+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcf%2F74%2F0b3679a4474a8a8f96fae6a8ee72%2Fkimdeal-wide-d6096c82910f34fc30b8d9cb7a8af56b8e2c2fe8.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/599x337+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcf%2F74%2F0b3679a4474a8a8f96fae6a8ee72%2Fkimdeal-wide-d6096c82910f34fc30b8d9cb7a8af56b8e2c2fe8.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/599x337+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcf%2F74%2F0b3679a4474a8a8f96fae6a8ee72%2Fkimdeal-wide-d6096c82910f34fc30b8d9cb7a8af56b8e2c2fe8.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/599x337+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcf%2F74%2F0b3679a4474a8a8f96fae6a8ee72%2Fkimdeal-wide-d6096c82910f34fc30b8d9cb7a8af56b8e2c2fe8.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/599x337+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcf%2F74%2F0b3679a4474a8a8f96fae6a8ee72%2Fkimdeal-wide-d6096c82910f34fc30b8d9cb7a8af56b8e2c2fe8.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/599x337+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcf%2F74%2F0b3679a4474a8a8f96fae6a8ee72%2Fkimdeal-wide-d6096c82910f34fc30b8d9cb7a8af56b8e2c2fe8.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/599x337+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcf%2F74%2F0b3679a4474a8a8f96fae6a8ee72%2Fkimdeal-wide-d6096c82910f34fc30b8d9cb7a8af56b8e2c2fe8.jpg" class="img" alt="Musician/singer Kim Deal of The Pixies performs at Hammerstein Ballroom on November 23, 2009, in New York City." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Musician/singer Kim Deal of The Pixies performs at Hammerstein Ballroom on November 23, 2009, in New York City.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Stephen Lovekin/Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Kim Deal has been in two storied rock bands since the 1980s&lt;/strong&gt;: The Pixies and The Breeders. Now, almost 40 years into her music career, she has released her first solo album, &lt;em&gt;Nobody Loves You More&lt;/em&gt;. Deal talks with &lt;em&gt;Morning Edition&lt;/em&gt; guest host Rob Schmitz about how a gifted ukulele shaped one of her new songs, the loss of people in her life and her overall musical journey. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧 &lt;strong&gt;Listen to snippets of Deal's newest songs and hear&lt;/strong&gt; what she had to say about &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=nx-s1-5002031:nx-s1-5262281-1"&gt;her new album&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Deep dive&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-35558" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 2120;         --source-height: 1193;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2120x1193+0+37/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%